# ChangeLog for app-backup/bacula
# Copyright 1999-2015 Gentoo Foundation; Distributed under the GPL v2
# $Header: /var/cvsroot/gentoo-x86/app-backup/bacula/ChangeLog,v 1.179 2015/06/09 09:01:25 jlec Exp $

  09 Jun 2015; Justin Lecher <jlec@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Updating remote-id in metadata.xml

  06 May 2015; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r4.ebuild,
  bacula-5.2.13-r3.ebuild, -bacula-7.0.5.ebuild, bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Migrate to USE=sqlite (bug #548646)

  06 May 2015; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> -bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  -bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Remove old versions depending on old python.eclass, but keep unstable
  revisions depending on the new python-single-r1 for users which need an old
  bacula client.

  19 Apr 2015; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  x86 stable wrt bug #529394

  17 Apr 2015; Mikle Kolyada <zlogene@gentoo.org> bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  sparc stable wrt bug #529394

  02 Mar 2015; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for ppc, wrt bug #529394

  23 Feb 2015; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-5.0.3-r4.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-7.0.5.ebuild, bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Update bundled libtools (bug #466696)

*bacula-5.2.13-r3 (23 Feb 2015)
*bacula-5.0.3-r4 (23 Feb 2015)

  23 Feb 2015; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-5.0.3-r4.ebuild,
  -bacula-5.2.12.ebuild, -bacula-5.2.13-r2.ebuild, +bacula-5.2.13-r3.ebuild,
  -bacula-7.0.2.ebuild, -bacula-7.0.4.ebuild:
  Move to python-single-r1. Drop old

  31 Jan 2015; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #529394

  28 Dec 2014; Aaron W. Swenson <titanofold@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-5.2.12.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13-r2.ebuild,
  bacula-7.0.2.ebuild, bacula-7.0.4.ebuild, bacula-7.0.5.ebuild,
  bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Rename virtual/postgresql to dev-db/postgresql

*bacula-7.0.5-r1 (28 Nov 2014)

  28 Nov 2014; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-7.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Fixes systemd tmpfile for bacula-clientonly (bug #528398). Thanks for
  reporting to D. Griffin

  03 Nov 2014; Aaron W. Swenson <titanofold@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-5.2.12.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13-r2.ebuild,
  bacula-7.0.2.ebuild, bacula-7.0.4.ebuild, bacula-7.0.5.ebuild:
  Update PostgreSQL dependencies and/or checks to virtual/postgresql.

*bacula-7.0.5 (16 Aug 2014)

  16 Aug 2014; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-7.0.5.ebuild:
  Bugfix release

*bacula-7.0.4 (21 Jun 2014)

  21 Jun 2014; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-7.0.4.ebuild:
  Bugfix release

*bacula-7.0.2 (10 Apr 2014)

  10 Apr 2014; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-7.0.2.ebuild,
  +files/7.0.2/bacula-7.0.2-depend.patch,
  +files/7.0.2/bacula-7.0.2-fix-static.patch:
  Major version bump

  05 Apr 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13-r2.ebuild:
  Alias value is not really needed here, bug #504370 by Fabian Koster

*bacula-5.2.13-r2 (01 Feb 2014)

  01 Feb 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +bacula-5.2.13-r2.ebuild,
  -bacula-5.2.13-r1.ebuild:
  Fix systemd unit files, bug #497748

*bacula-5.2.13-r1 (11 Jan 2014)

  11 Jan 2014; Pacho Ramos <pacho@gentoo.org> +bacula-5.2.13-r1.ebuild:
  Install upstream unit files (#497748 by Khumba)

  20 May 2013; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-5.2.12.ebuild, bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Remove HPPA keywording (bug #409229).

  01 May 2013; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Fix logrotate config file (bug 258187, comment #4). Thanks Ortwin.

  23 Apr 2013; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Fix desktop file category (bug #466688). Use CXXFLAGS instead CFLAGS (bug
  466694). Thanks ago for reporting

  22 Apr 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Stable for sparc, wrt bug #466636

  22 Apr 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Stable for ppc, wrt bug #466636

  21 Apr 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Stable for x86, wrt bug #466636

  21 Apr 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #466636

*bacula-5.2.13 (14 Mar 2013)

  14 Mar 2013; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-5.2.13.ebuild:
  Version bump.
  Add USE=examples as requested by bug #457504.
  Add info about state of SQLite support (bug #445540).

  02 Mar 2013; Markos Chandras <hwoarang@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-5.2.12.ebuild:
  Move Qt dependencies to the new category

  13 Jan 2013; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for x86, wrt bug #447608

  30 Dec 2012; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for sparc, wrt bug #447608

  22 Dec 2012; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for ppc, wrt bug #447608

  21 Dec 2012; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  bacula-5.2.12.ebuild:
  Make build log verbose - simplified version (bug 447806). Thanks hasufell.

  20 Dec 2012; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for amd64, wrt bug #447608

  20 Dec 2012; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild:
  Fix to respect CXX and CXXFLAGS (bug #447728 and 447730). Make build log
  verbose (bug #447806). Fix problems with USE=static. Switch to EAPI=5 and
  REQUIRED_USE. Thanks ago and peratu

  18 Dec 2012; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild:
  Stable for HPPA (bug #447608).

  10 Oct 2012; Thomas Beierlein <tomjbe@gentoo.org> +bacula-5.0.3-r3.ebuild,
  +files/5.0.3/bacula-5.0.3-cve.patch:
  Readd bacula-5.0.3 including fix for CVE-2012-4430 to enable use with older
  bacula directors.

  23 Sep 2012; Agostino Sarubbo <ago@gentoo.org> -bacula-5.0.3-r2.ebuild,
  -bacula-5.2.5.ebuild:
  Remove old

  23 Sep 2012; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> bacula-5.2.12.ebuild:
  sparc/x86 stable wrt #434878

  23 Sep 2012; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> bacula-5.0.3-r2.ebuild:
  Marked ~hppa (bug #434878).

